The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 London, June 21: Switzerlands Xstrata wants talks with mining rival Anglo American of the UK about a proposed merger of equals worth about $68 billion, seeking increased scale and cost synergies, Xstrata said. Anglo is likely to resist the attempt by Xstrata to forge a larger mining group better able to compete with bigger competitors BHP Billiton, Vale and Rio Tinto, a source close to the situation said.                            
	 Calcutta, June 21: Credit rating agency Icra is planning to increase its income from the non-rating business to bring it on a par with the rating business over the next two years. At present, the rating business contributes 60 per cent of its revenue, while non-rating activities make up for the remaining 40 per cent.                             
	 New Delhi, June 21: The countrys infotech industry is expected to grow at 10.8 per cent in 2009, the lowest in the last five years, because of the global economic meltdown, a report by analyst firm IDC India has said. But in the next four years, it will grow at 13.9 per cent to touch a revenue of $110 billion.                            
	 New Delhi, June 21: Thai authorities are about to slap up to 32 per cent anti-dumping duty on the import of a vital steel product from India. The Indian government is yet to impose a similar curb on inflows from China, Ukraine, Egypt and other countries.                            
	 New Delhi, June 21: Electric vehicles manufacturer Lohia Auto is looking to sell 10,000 units of its e-bikes  FAME and OMA  by the end of this fiscal year.                                                                                                                           
